zzapper wrote:
> Any improvments?

>    if [ "$files" != "" ]

It would probably be more standard to rewrite this as

if [[ ${#files} -gt 0 ]]

or equivalently

if (( ${#files} ))

which test whether there are any elements in the array.  However, in
practice what you have will work fine, since a zero-length filename
is meaningless.

pws


